<br>
I think you are attempting to characterize my objection as RP hysteria, and also to gloss over the nature of the 'advice.'<br>
<br>
I did not rant on with a slew of !!!!! and therefore don't need to 'relax.'<br>
<br>
Such gems as (paraphrase) 'Shadow Knights don't even bother trying to be a puller till you're 60, leave it to the Monks.'<br>
and 'Casters if you melee you'll get a bad rep and wind up soloing your high level days because no one will group with you' and 'Monks the entirety of your existence is to Pull.  Dedicate yourself to learning everything about every mob to be able to pull' are NOT just useful tidbits like always use Assist, and play your class effectively and combine strengths with other classes.<br>
<br>
What they are is a Formula that says 'After 3 years in Production the EQ community has determined that these are the OOC Roles each class should play in a fight.  This will give you the optimum damage/minute and Mana Efficiency, allowing you to kill mobs quick with minimal downtime.  It has nothing to do with Characters of Roleplay.  It is about how YOU the Player utilize your Avatar in order to defeat the Mob AI.  If you ignore this you won't get along in the 'real' world of EQ.<br>
<br>
Am I saying that his observations are wrong?  No!  But what I am reminding people is that for many people they are looking for a little different experience on FV than being the most 'efficient.' <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ualyissa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alyissa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/22/02 3:21:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=398.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Oh, you want general?</span><hr size=1> No, it's simply that your objection comes off as being:<br>
