<br>
I definitely keep track of the average length of fight and use that to gauge whether my mana would be better spent DoT or Blam.  I used to DoT everything almost right off, but it's turned out to be far more mana efficient to just pop off a lightning or two in some groups.  Also, I'm not afraid to use Stinging Swarm instead of Creeping Crud when appropriate -- more mana efficient when there are multiple fights that aren't hairy enough to require the tougher spell.  Of course, if the group is very efficient and I'm the healer, I tend to save most my mana for heals while Kenyon dishes out the blammo.<br>
<br>
If you have the time (and focus), run a quick tally of how many hits get off on the tank with your damage shield up to get a good gauge of how much damage it's doing vs. lightning or a DoT.  This is another time when the lower level spell could do the job, too, when mana's tight.  Of course, if there's multiples, I'd always recommend your best damage shield to increase the chances that the next time you heal, one of them doesn't decide to make you their new best friend...<br>
<br>
